Questionnaire Report for Lobster Fishery

(MERA version 5.4.3)

Duranta Kembaren (dd.kembaren@gmail.com)

2019-11-26


About this document

This is a prototype of an automatic report that documents how the user specified the operating model and their various justifications.


Introduction

  1. Lobster fishery in the southern coast of Yogyakarta and Pacitan was utilizing using gillnet and trap (local: krendet) and mostly using and mostly of them are small-scale fishery. Describe the history and current status of the fishery, including fleets, sectors, vessel types and practices/gear by vessel type, landing ports, economics/markets, whether targeted/bycatch, other stocks caught in the fishery.

  2. Describe the stock’s ecosystem functions, dependencies, and habitat types.

  3. Provide all relevant reference materials, such as assessments, research, and other analysis.

Management Characteristics

Types of fishery management that are possible

Answered
TAC (Total Allowable Catch): a catch limit
TAE (Total Allowable Effort): an effort limit
Size limit
Time-area closures (a marine reserve)
Justification
1. TAC=776 mt per year; minimum legal size: CL= >8 cm, W= > 200 g

2. Minimum legal size start on 2015

3. Directorate General of Surveillance and Agency of Fish Quarantine had mandate to monitor the size limit of catch. This regulation quite easy to apply for the export trading since they need a certified document but for the local trading it was unmonitored.

4. Describe and reference any legal/policy requirements for management, monitoring and enforcement.
